flowRoot.flowPara: When dragged, a thumbnail will move along the axis of any joined edges. To detach it from its joined edges, it must be pulled away in an opposing direction.
When a thumbnail has been detached, it can be freely dragged. Any other displays automatically rearrange so that there aren't gaps between them.

flowRoot.flowPara: Shared edges don't have "corners" - it isn't possible to change direction when dragging a thumbnail that is attached to another. In the following example, it wouldn't be possible to move the thumbnail to the left, other than to detach it from the joined edge it shares with the other display.

flowRoot.flowPara: - Releasing the drag while the thumbnail is in an invalid position restores the previous arrangement
- The thumbnail will stick to the edges of the other thumbnails if they are moved close to oneanother

Here, the solid red line indicates the axis of movement in parallel to the thumnbail's joined edges. The dotted line indicates the threshold that the pointer must pass in order to detach the thumbnail:
Free-drag mode ends when an edge of the dragged thumbnail comes into contact with the edge of another thumbnail.
